  </section>

  <section
    class="section4 py-10 md:py-40 overflow-x-hidden"
    style="background-color: #efefef;"
  >
    <div class="container">
      <div
        class="flex mx-auto flex-col items-start md:items-center justify-center"
      >
        <h1 style="font-size: xx-large;">
          Platform Engineering Consulting Services by Improwised Technologies
        </h1>
      </div>

      <section class="py-16 my-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
              The Strategic Evolution After DevOps
            </h2>
            <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-primary-500 mt-3 rounded"></div>
          </div>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Platform engineering services have become the best answer for companies who are having trouble with the cloud's complexity, increased operating expenses, and low developer productivity.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Traditional DevOps methods frequently lead to fragmented toolchains. Platform engineering, on the other hand, creates standardized, <a  class="underline decoration-indigo-500" target="_blank" href="https://www.improwised.com/blog/internal-developer-platforms-reduce-deployment-times/">self-service developer platforms</a> that hide the complexity of infrastructure while still following organizational rules.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="py-16 my-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
              What is the real difference between platform engineering and DevOps?
